Approval gates and developer choices happen inside each skill.

1. **Feature planning contracts** — From PRD or scope, produce reviewable Master / Phase / PR plan bodies per Sedea development-process templates (`planner`, `phase-planner`, `pr-plan`).

2. **Ad-hoc plan and delivery** — For smaller, well-bounded requests: shorter ad-hoc PRD (`ad-hoc-prd`), plans under `.sedea/operations/`, expedited Master Plan → one or more PR plans when the phase layer is not needed. All checks and verifications remain mandatory.

3. **Scope breakdown** — Keep deliverable complexity under control: break work into delivery phases or PRs with explicit lists and assessments (`delivery-phases`, `pr-breakdown`, `new-plan` indexed spawn). Parent lists show **all** phases/PRs at high level with `_TBD_` links until eligible; **depth-first expansion** gates the next row on **ship-complete** predecessors — phases always sequential; PRs follow **`### Sequencing`** stages per **development-process.md** § *Depth-first plan-tree traversal*.

4. **Implementation** — Plan-anchored coding sessions: completeness gate, worktrees, sidecar state, Sedea workbench attach, copy-safe agent prompts (`coding-session`).

5. **PR and review closure** — Open PRs with reviewer-complete context (`create-pr`); run pre-PR review (`pre-pr-review`); triage and resolve review threads (`pr-review`).

6. **Deploy verification** — Walk deploy-test plan checklists; record status and capstone todos in the plan file (`deploy-walk`).

7. **Post-ship plan hygiene** — Merge-driven reconcile, archive candidates, follow-ups triage (`plan-reconcile`).

8. **Plan tree integrity** — Scaffold and link `.plan.md` + `.state.yaml` under `.sedea/operations/` (`new-plan`, `plan-reconcile`); valid parents, slugs, Mission Control metadata (`mission.yaml` when listed). **All operations writes from the main hosting clone only** — see *Operations filesystem invariant*.

### Operations filesystem invariant (binding)

All artifacts under **`.sedea/operations/`** — plans (`*.plan.md`, `*.state.yaml`), dispatch bundles, docs, and any other operations-tree paths — **must be created and edited only from the main hosting repo clone**: the filesystem tree whose root contains **`.sedea/centers/sedea/`** (primary clone / Mission Control workspace root). **Never** create, edit, move, or delete operations files with shell **`cwd`**, editor roots, or paths resolved from a **hosting repo git worktree**.

| Allowed | Forbidden |
|---------|-----------|
| Read operations paths from any lane for context | Write operations files from a worktree `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` |
| Run **`plan-state.mjs`** with `cd "$HOSTING_ROOT"`; pass **`--cwd "$WORKTREE_ROOT"`** only to **link** a plan to a worktree | Run **`plan-state.mjs set-*`** (or equivalent writes) with shell cwd inside a worktree |
| Update sidecars during **`coding-session`** after resolving **`HOSTING_ROOT`** explicitly | Bootstrap or persist operations content under a worktree copy |

Worktrees are **ephemeral**; operations artifacts must **persist** on the durable main clone. When a worktree lacks **`.sedea/operations/`**, **do not** treat it as the write surface — resolve the main hosting root first. Normative baseline: [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § **Operations persistence (main hosting root only)**; **`HOSTING_ROOT`** resolution: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc`](../../rules/20_efficient-pr-shipping.mdc) § *Resolve `HOSTING_ROOT`*.

