## Hub missionInputs

Sedea Hub may dispatch **`plan and deliver`** with an optional `missionInputs` bag on `RequestDispatchMissionCommand`. The Hub host validates the bag against this block when present; missions without this section skip validation (Centers and manual dispatches unchanged).

| key | required |
| --- | --- |
| `parentSlug` | yes |
| `parentPlanPath` | yes |

- **`parentSlug`** — operations plan slug for the roadmap topic row the developer chose (**Start New Plan** on a `top_level_topic` with `parentSlug === null`). Hub sends this key; the host resolves **`parentPlanPath`** under `.sedea/operations/.../plans/` before validation.
- **`parentPlanPath`** — workspace-relative path to the parent `.plan.md` (host-populated from **`parentSlug`**). Mission Control renders it in the Squad Leader opening message (see **§4** *Hub parent in opening message*).

**Centers vs Hub:** **Start New Plan** from Sedea Hub includes **`parentSlug`** (and resolved **`parentPlanPath`** in `dispatch.yaml`). Centers mission launch and manual **`plan and deliver`** dispatches omit **`missionInputs`** — §4 parent **AskQuestion** behavior is unchanged when no Hub parent section appears in the opening message. See **`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/docs/development-process.md`** § *Sedea Hub Start New Plan vs Centers dispatch*.

